  481                                                       ;The following subroutine is used to
  482                                                       ;input characters from the system's
  483                                                       ;input device (such as a keyboard)
  484                                                       ;into the LINE INPUT BUFFER. Routine has limited
  485                                                       ;editing capability included.
  486                                                       ;(Rubout = delete previous character(s) entered.)
  487  01EB  0E 00        STRIN:	MVI C,000H                      ;Initialize register C to zero.
  488  01ED  CD 6E 02     STRIN1:	CALL CINPUT                     ;Call user provided device input subroutine to fetch one
  489  01F0  FE FF        	CPI 0FFH                        ;Character from the input device. Is it ASCII code for
  490  01F2  C2 04 02     	JNZ NOTDEL                      ;Rubout? Skip to next section if not rubout.
  491  01F5  3E DC        	MVI A,0DCH                      ;Else, load ASCII code for backslash into ACC.
  492  01F7  CD 60 02     	CALL ECHO                       ;Call user display driver to present backslash as a delete
  493  01FA  0D           	DCR C                           ;Indicator. Now decrement the input character counter.
  494  01FB  FA EB 01     	JM STRIN                        ;If at beginning of line do NOT decrement H and L.
  495  01FE  CD 52 02     	CALL DEC                        ;Else, decrement H & L line pointer to erase previous
  496  0201  C3 ED 01     	JMP STRIN1                      ;Entry, then go back for a new input.
